22/01/2009
NICOSIA, Cyprus -- President Demetris Christofias on Wednesday (January 21st) stepped down as leader of his ruling Communist Party, AKEL, giving way to Andros Kyprianou.
The move marked the first shift in AKEL's command in 20 years.
Christofias, whose mandate as president expires in 2013, said he will remain a member of the party.
(Reuters, Famagusta Gazette, Xinhua - 21/01/09)
